In order to be recognized as an accepted training institution for detection of deception examiners by the cabinet, a polygraph examiner's school must offer at least two hundred and forty (240) hours of classroom training and instruction consisting of, but not limited to, the following subjects:
Instrumentation of the instrument prescribed in KRS 329.020;
Psychology;
Physiology;
Question formulation;
Chart interpretation;
Interrogation;
History and legal ethics of the polygraph;
Supervised practice examinations; and
Any other courses necessary to assure adequate training of detection of deception examiners.
